#compdef weylus
# ============================================================================
# weylus - Use your iPad / Android tablet as a graphic tablet (Rust, AGPL-3.0-or-later)
#
# Author : HMH (henry@freedesk.net) - H-M-H on GitHub
# Upstream: https://github.com/H-M-H/Weylus
#
# weylus runs a small HTTP + WebSocket server on a desktop machine
# (Linux / macOS / Windows) that streams the screen as video to a
# browser on a tablet (iPad / Android) and accepts pen + touch input
# back over the wire, turning the tablet into a Wacom-like graphic
# tablet for the desktop. The server URL is communicated to the
# tablet via an on-screen QR code generated at startup by the
# `qrcode` crate.
#
# The QR code emission lane is built on `qrcode = "0.14.0"` (declared
# verbatim at upstream Cargo.toml HEAD), the canonical Rust QR
# encoder by kennytm (github.com/kennytm/qrcode-rust, 500+ stars).
# It implements QR Code Model 2 spec (ISO/IEC 18004) end-to-end:
# Reed-Solomon error correction (levels L/M/Q/H), Galois field
# arithmetic over GF(256), eight masking patterns, alignment +
# timing patterns, version selection (1 - 40), and the four
# encoding modes (numeric, alphanumeric, byte, kanji). The crate
# exposes a `QrCode::new(data)` builder + a renderer to ASCII,
# SVG, or pixel buffer.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 199 :: QR CODE GENERATION (ISO/IEC 18004 - QR Model 2)
# Round 1295 :: Rust slot 1 of 4 :: OPENS Axis 199
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis (proposed):
#   Rust    : kennytm/qrcode-rust                            - Model 2 + RS encoder
#   Go      : skip2/go-qrcode                                - Model 2 + RS encoder
#   TS/Node : soldair/node-qrcode                            - Model 2 + RS encoder
#
# All three are clean-room QR encoders that target the same ISO/IEC
# 18004 spec but were built independently. kennytm in Rust is the
# library you reach for when you want a typed QR builder with no
# C/FFI deps; skip2/go-qrcode in Go is the dominant pure-Go
# implementation (8000+ stars on github.com/skip2/go-qrcode); and
# soldair/node-qrcode is the dependency-of-record for the JavaScript
# ecosystem (~8M weekly npm downloads), used by everything from
# Stripe checkout pages to two-factor auth setup flows that need
# to render a QR for an `otpauth://` URI.
#
# weylus is a real consumer outside the "auth setup + URL deep link"
# common case - it generates a QR at server startup that encodes the
# `http://<bind-addr>:<port>/?access_code=<code>` URL so the tablet
# can join the session with a single camera scan rather than typing
# the address. Exercises the QrCode::new + ASCII-render path of
# qrcode-rust; the same idiom appears in WireGuard QR provisioning,
# Tailscale auth, and the otpauth provisioning URIs used by Aegis
# and Authy.
# ============================================================================

_weylus() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '--access-code[set the access code (token) required to join the session]:code:' \
        '--bind-address[address to bind the HTTP server to (default 0.0.0.0)]:ip:' \
        '--web-port[HTTP port for the web UI (default 1701)]:port:' \
        '--try-vaapi[Linux: try VA-API hardware video acceleration]' \
        '--try-nvenc[Linux/Windows: try NVIDIA NVENC GPU video encoding]' \
        '--try-videotoolbox[macOS: try VideoToolbox hardware video acceleration]' \
        '--try-mediafoundation[Windows: try MediaFoundation hardware video acceleration]' \
        '--auto-start[start the server immediately at GUI launch]' \
        '--gui-theme[GUI theme]:theme:(light dark system)' \
        '--no-gui[run server without GUI; start immediately]' \
        '--wayland-support[Linux: enable Wayland / PipeWire screen capture]' \
        '--print-index-html[print the templated index.html served by Weylus]' \
        '--print-access-html[print access.html served by Weylus]' \
        '--print-style-css[print style.css served by Weylus]' \
        '--print-lib-js[print lib.js served by Weylus]' \
        '--custom-index-html[use a custom index.html template]:file:_files -g "*.html"' \
        '--custom-access-html[use a custom access.html]:file:_files -g "*.html"' \
        '--custom-style-css[use a custom style.css]:file:_files -g "*.css"' \
        '--custom-lib-js[use a custom lib.js]:file:_files -g "*.js"' \
        '--completions[print shell completion script]:shell:(bash zsh fish powershell elvish)' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]'
}

_weylus "$@"
